<TITLE> DMP updates criminal database, crackdown 'soon' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)The Dhaka city police have updated the database on criminals and will crack down on them 'soon', its chief said on Tuesday. In the monthly meeting at Rajarbagh police telecom auditorium Dhaka Metropolitan Police commissioner ASM Shahidul Haque voiced concerned abut the security. "We are trying to take control of the situation and will start the operation soon." He said people who commit crimes on cell phone were difficult to identify. "Often they do not own the numbers they call from. We will sit with mobile-phone operators on how to identify them." A police officer provided bdnews24.com with some details of database on condition of anonymity. He said the list includes 506 killers, 119 robbers, 481 muggers, 91 'Aagyan Party/ Molom Party members', 407 illegal arms owner, 74 bomb-makers, 553 gangsters and extortionists, 72 land grabbers, 477 drug peddlers and 292 other criminals. bdn
